    • Method Detail

      • addEdge

        public boolean addEdge(Edge e)
        Adds a given edge to the Graph and returns whether it didn't already belong to the graph before the call. Note that the graph will not be modified if the edge already belongs to the Graph, i.e there is an edge e' such that e' belongs to the Graph and e.equals(e')
        Parameters:
        e - The edge to add to the graph
        Returns:
        true if the edge didn't belong to the graph before the call
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if e is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one or both nodes of the edge don't belong to the graph

      • addNode

        public void addNode(Node n)
        Adds a node to the graph. Note that the node must not belong to the Graph before the call i.e there must not be any node n' belonging to the Graph such that n.equals(n')
        Parameters:
        n - The node to add to the graph
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the node n already belongs to the graph

      • containsEdge

        public boolean containsEdge(Edge e)
        Returns whether the Graph contains a given Edge formed by nodes belonging to the graph.
        Parameters:
        e - The edge to test for belonging to the graph
        Returns:
        true if there exists an edge e' such that it belongs to the graph and e.equals(e')
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if e is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one or both nodes of the edge e don't belong to the graph

        public java.util.Set<Edge> getAdjacencyList(Node n)
        Returns a non-modifiable version of the adjacency list of a given node.
        Parameters:
        n - The node whose adjacency list is requested
        Returns:
        a non-modifiable set with the adjacent edges of the node n' such that n' belongs to the graph and n.equals(n')
        Throws:

      • removeEdge

        public abstract boolean removeEdge(Node n1,
                                   Node n2)
        Removes an edge identified by two nodes n1, n2 from the graph and returns whether the edge was in the graph before the call. The edge to be removed is such that it belongs to the graph and it contains two nodes n1', n2' such that n1.equals(n1') and n2.equals(n2') or n1.equals(n2') and n2.equals(n1')
        Parameters:
        n1 - One of the nodes of the edge to remove
        n2 - The other node of the edge to remove
        Returns:
        true if the edge belonged to the graph before the removal try
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if n1 is null or n2 is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one or both nodes of the edge don't belong to the graph

      • removeNode

        public boolean removeNode(Node n)
        Removes a given node n' from the graph if it belonged to the Graph and returns whether it belonged (i.e whether the graph has been modified by the call). The node n' is such that n.equals(n')
        Parameters:
        n - the node to remove from the graph
        Returns:
        true if the node belonged to the graph before the removal try

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns a string representation of the graph. First the Graph order and number of edges are printed in the same line, followed by the list of nodes of the graph, followed by the list of edges of the graph. The string ends with a new line.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a string representation of the graph.
